The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 02 November is 94,054 (10,840.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 28 October, there were 4,587 new confirmed cases (528.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 21 October, there were 4,422 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 4% (165 extra cases).
